data.description: Natural light heaven! A Colonial Style home in West Henrico has a lot of parking space directly in front in the quite & peaceful cul-de-sac. Two porches in the front! You enter with a comforting view of the living room with a cozy wood burning fireplace. On the left is a formal guest/dining room or a office/1st floor bedroom. A large kitchen and separated eat-in area with sky lights, hidden laundry closet, and 1st floor 1/2 bath and peaceful view of the backyard. A nice deck at the back for you to enjoy the outdoors and private backyard. At just under 1/4 of an acre you will have the perfect amount of yard, enough to be a private sanctuary but not too much to be a weekend burden. 3 formal bedrooms upstairs including a huge primary suite with a giant walk-in closet and full bath. The other bedrooms upstairs are well-lit and spacious with a full hall bath. This home has an outdoor storage area for lawn tools, a pull down attic, a pantry and closets galore. Close to everything you'll need: new residential & retail developments recently completed nearby, hip restaurants at Libbie Mill, and moments from the highway. Centrally located with easy access to all Richmond areas.
